Tents offered to floods victims in Guizhou Province
2011-06-08 07:31:15 GMT
More than 30 tents have been erected  in Wangmo County, southwest China's Guizhou Province to temporarily settle 100 victims. By June 7, the rain-triggered floods here have caused 14 deaths and left 35 people missing. The flood also damaged 5,500 hectares of cropland, washed away more than 500 vehicles, toppled 100 homes and destroyed roads and bridges. 
